SIMPLE: pursuance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pursuance
<hw>Pur*su"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Pursuant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of pursuing or
prosecuting; a following out or after.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sermons are not like curious inquiries after new nothings, but
<qex>pursuances</qex> of old truths.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being pursuant; consequence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>In pursuance of</b></col>, <cd>in accordance with; in
prosecution or fulfillment of.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pursuant</ent>⟦br⟧
